cs.SI, cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.CE 

This paper deals with the analysis of web services using complex network analysis techniques. The paper focuses on the syntactic and semantic approaches used to describe web services and their dependencies. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely sub-categories include cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
